word_mean_info__list.difference: 特指有某项专长，有某方面经验。
通常指已掌握某行业的专业技能或手段，或已有从事某一专门工作的本领或技术。
指在工作或操作中表现出灵巧、熟练。
多指擅长于某事，侧重技艺或科学方面。

bilingual.source: Skilled sailors race small sailing boats across oceans.
bilingual.target: 熟练的水手驾驶小帆船横渡海洋。
她是一名熟练的打字员。
貂是一个熟练的攀爬者。

bilingual.source: You need skilled driving to pass this test.
bilingual.target: 你需要熟练的驾驶技术才能通过这个考试。

bilingual.source: He is a skilled swinger on the dance floor.
bilingual.target: 他是舞池里一个熟练的摇摆者。

bilingual.source: As a skilled hider, he always wins the game.
bilingual.target: 作为一个熟练的躲藏者，他总是赢得比赛。

bilingual.source: My friend recommended a very skilled oculist.
bilingual.target: 我的朋友推荐了一位非常熟练的眼科医生。

bilingual.source: We need a skilled stitcher to finish this job.
bilingual.target: 我们需要一个熟练的缝纫工来完成这项工作。

bilingual.source: The spa hired a new masseuse who is very skilled.
bilingual.target: 这家水疗中心雇了一位非常熟练的新女按摩师。

list.abstract: 娴熟（英文：adept），读音xián shú，汉语词语，指熟练。例句有“他脚法娴熟，射门准确，不愧为球星”。 相关作品有“她娴熟的手法，就跟旋着的风车那么好看。”出自伊凡的《 没有了猪的猪栏 》 ，近义词有纯熟、稔熟、熟练，反义词有生疏、生硬。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, unless of course he's a skilled hypnotist.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果他是催眠大师，那可说不准。

yingyinNormal.en: Charming, smart, and very skilled at combat. Especially in water.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他迷人，聪明，战术技巧非常高超，尤其在水中。

yingyinNormal.en: How can you do that? Because I am the most skilled extractor.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你怎么做到? 因为我就是最技艺超凡的盗梦者。

yingyinNormal.en: She's hunting him. Skilled at surveillance and she fights like a pro.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她在追捕他，监视熟练，搏斗专业。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, also, if they did have coitus, we'll all be needing a skilled psychiatrist.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而且，如果他们真的交媾了，我们都需要个厉害的心理医生开导。

yingyinNormal.en: Mr. Saito, we can train your subconscious to defend itself from even the most skilled extractor.
yingyinNormal.zh: 齐藤先生，我们训练你潜意识防卫，去抵抗技艺超凡的盗梦者。

yingyinNormal.en: Because, Raphael, The Shredder is a skilled warrior whose cruelty is ever-reaching! And you are just teenagers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拉斐尔，因为施莱德是经验丰富的武士，前所未有的残忍，而你们还是未成年。

yingyinNormal.en: But this year you'll be facing other Victors. Capitol favorites. Smart, cunning, skilled. And they all know one another.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是今年你们的对手是以往的冠军，国会区的明星们，他们聪明，狡猾，训练有素而且都彼此相熟。

yingyinNormal.en: It's time for us to invest in educational opportunity, to guarantee that we have the most highly skilled workforce in the world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们应该加大教育领域投资，让国民接受良好教育，保证我们拥有全世界最优秀的劳动力队伍。

yingyinNormal.en: This traditional art still thrives even in 21st-century Hong Kong, where the city's skilled Dragon dancers are always highly sought after.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在21世纪的香港，这一传统民俗仍旧盛行，技术娴熟的舞龙艺人始终凤毛麟角。

yingyinNormal.en: It was not hard to be moved by the dedication of the highly skilled doctors, paramedics and crew, who are called-out on average five times a day.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们无法不被那些技术精湛的医生，护士和军人所感动，这些人每天至少要紧急出动五次以上。
